{
  "texts": [
    "(16)To solve this, the problem is reframed as a regression task.",
    "The operator A is approximated by minimizing the Frobenius norm of the difference between X and AX.",
    "This minimization can be performed using the Moore-Penrose pseudoinverse X † (see, e.g., [38]):A = arg min A ||X -AX|| F = X X †.",
    "(17)Once the operator is identified, it can be used to propagate the dynamics forward in time, approximating the next state x(t i+1) using the current state x(t i):x(t i+1) ≈ Ax(t i).",
    "(18)This framework, is however, only valid for linear dynamics."
  ]
}